An **object** is a collection of related data and functions, organized with **keys** and **values**.

```javascript
let person = {
  name: 'Alice',
  age: 25,
  city: 'New York'
};
```

Objects use **curly braces** { }, and each property is `key: value`.

blocks.code:
let book = {
  title: 'JavaScript for Beginners',
  author: 'John Doe',
  year: 2023,
  pages: 350
};

console.log(book);

let car = {
  brand: 'Toyota',
  model: 'Camry',
  year: 2020,
  color: 'blue'
};

console.log('Brand:', car.brand);
console.log('Color:', car['color']);
console.log('Year:', car.year);

let user = {
  name: 'Bob',
  score: 0,
  level: 1
};

console.log('Initial:', user);

user.score = 100;  // Update
user.level = 2;    // Update
user.country = 'USA';  // Add new property

console.log('Updated:', user);
